u art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["1  ♂ ‘Wondrous’ or ‘enlightenment’.","2  ♀ ‘Fine jade’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Pierre II d’Arsac was born in 1150, in Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France as the son of Pierre Ier d’Arsac. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"1150–":"1150–Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","1180":"1180","Arsac, Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1150–":"1150–Kuollut","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","1180":"1180","Arsac, Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Ranska"},"fr":{"1150–":"1150–Décédé","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","1180":"1180","Arsac, Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France","lifeSummary":"Pierre II d’Arsac est né en 1150, à Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France, fils de Pierre Ier d’Arsac. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1150–":"1150–Verstorben","1150–Male":"1150–Verstorben","1180–Male":"1180–Verstorben","1120–Male":"1120–Verstorben","1120":"1120","1150":"1150","1180":"1180","Arsac, Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France":"Lesparre-Médoc, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Pierre II d’Arsac wurde 1150 in Lesparre-